description: ** Architecturally Stunning 2 bed duplex apartment ** ABC are delighted to announce the release of this delightful open plan apartment converted from the previous All Saints Church Hall, spread over two floors of this unique building which not only possesses great character but is also set within a highly desireable location and only a short distance from Sydenham Station. Benefitting from secure, underground allocated parking and phone entry system.PROPERTY HISTORY & LOCATION The old All Saints Church Hall was converted into apartments with a new and higher roof line but has managed to retain the distinctive church stump of the original church spire with the new All Saints Church Hall and Church is located on the right hand side.The high end conversion has resulted in there now being a small number of exquisite apartments created and just occasionally one is available for letting.Located on Trewsbury Road, in close proximeity to both Sydenham Overground and Penge East rail.PROPERTY DESCRIPTION This two double bedroom church conversion has accommodation over the first and second floors, benefitting from a wide range of striking features with the original beams evident throughout.Vaulted ceilings make these generous rooms appear even larger with expansive velux windows making the living space light but cosy and perfect for entertaining.Throughout the apartment there are reminders of the history of this building giving the rooms character rarely seen in rental accoommodation.The gable end of the building still retains the original feature window which can be seen from the attached photographs.COMMUNAL AREAS:Please note that there has been a leak within the communal areas as one enters the building which is to be repaired and redecorated as soon as possible.  The source of the leak has been repaired. 11.01.23ACCOMMODATION Spread over two floors the apartment benefits from a magnificant open plan lounge / kitchen / diner with ample space for all aspects of day to day living.One can enjoy the views from the stunning arched inset windows that sit magnificently side by side in this delightfully vaulted ceiling, beamed living area. Benefitting from laminate floor throughout this open space, stairs to the second floor level.  The open plan kitchen diner is spacious with a wide range of both wall and floor units, complimentary worktops and tiled splashbacks.Integrated five ring gas hob and large 90cm electric oven with extractor fan over.The combi boiler which provides both heating and hot water is hidden away within the kitchen cupboard for easy access.To the second floor are two delightfully presented bedrooms both carpeted, the larger of the two benefitting from 2 large velux windows and beamed vaulted ceiling, the second bedroom again benefitting from velux window and angled walls making both rooms spacious and light.To the second floor is the bathroom, fitted with bath, wc and sink.  Bath is also fitted with overbath shower.  Flooring is laid to lino and large velux window.PROPERTY VIEWINGS Where possible, we have everything here on our adverts; from the property photographs and description to the video walkthroughs filmed by ourselves and the property floor plans. These should be able to help assist you in making your decision in renting a property with us. After viewing the videos available and reviewing all the advert content, you are more than welcome to raise any queries which we will do our best to answer for you.If, after you have viewed the video, you would like to view the property in person, please call our office to request a viewing. If we can offer a viewing, with 15-minute slots offered and our viewings are normally conducted during our office opening hours.Once you have made the decision to apply, our application procedure is explained fully below. You may of course, contact our office and request application forms be sent to you digitally at any time  even before viewing if you are eager to apply !! you can of course withdraw your application post viewing if you should so wish.APPLICATION PROCEDURE There is a requirement for each person aged 18 or over to fill in an application form. These along with the relevant guidance notes will be sent to you via our online system. Paper versions are available and can be dispatched by second class mail if you are unable to use the portal but could delay your application.ABC Property Shop have always operated a first come, first served system with property applications. At the point of application, you must submit all required documentation and application forms. We will not accept partly completed applications and may process another application if you have not submitted all required documentation.When you are completing your application form, please ensure that you supply as much supporting information as you can as this will speed up your application. DO I REQUIRE A GUARANTOR A guarantor is required for all our properties. The guarantor must have a disposable income or savings sufficient to cover your rent should you default along with the cost of any charges, legal fees, disrepair, or dilapidations that may be deemed your liability at the determination of the tenancy based on the results of inspections undertaken. The guarantor will remain in place for as long as your tenancy irrespective of whether you are resident in the property or not. The guarantors liability will only end on the legal ending of the tenancy and not before.Income may be determined by way of private income or salary, please email us for further information. Please note your guarantor will be subject to credit checks and other referencing to clarify that they will be suitable to stand as guarantor. A guarantor is a person who agrees, at the outset of the tenancy, to be jointly liable for any losses the landlord may incur that can be legally attributed to rent arrears, damage to the property or costs that may be incurred due to the behaviour of the tenants or the tenants visitors to the property  whether invited or not.This liability includes any matters arising from your vacation of the property too or post tenancy debt recovery.A guarantor will be required to complete application forms like the tenancy application forms and will need to ideally be aged between 25 & 65.  We may consider persons out of these age ranges, but acceptance is based purely on individual merit.HOLDING FEE Once you have submitted your application in full and this has been reviewed, we will ask you to pay your holding fee. This is equal to no more than one weeks rent.We will not commence processing your application until we have received your holding fee and the property will not be held until this is received.Your fee will not be refunded if you withdraw from renting the property, fail the Right to Rent check, provide false or misleading information or if we are unable to exchange signed contracts with 15 calendar days due to issues that can be deemed as your fault.MOVE IN DAY Once your processed application has been accepted by the landlord and ABC, you will be forwarded by email your acceptance letter which details the next stages. Please ensure you read this thoroughly and if you have any queries or questions take this opportunity to raise them.On receipt of your acceptance letter, please follow instructions to set a move in date for your tenancy to commence.Prior to move in day, you will receive your leases, guarantor deed and other relevant paperwork to sign online. Please ensure that you do read through the tenancy agreement and raise any queries with the staff prior to your move in day as time is limited during the completion procedure and we would prefer any queries to be dealt with prior to completion day.You will be required to pay the rent and deposit via bank transfer no later than 24 hours in advance. The funds due will be confirmed in your acceptance letter. DEPOSIT Your deposit is payable on or before the day you move in and will be a sum equal to somewhere between a months rent and five weeks rent dependent upon your situation and our clients requirements.PETS In apartments such as All Saints Court, pets are not allowed.YOUR DETAILS In compliance with General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), for general enquiries and viewings, your details will be retained by us for a period of no longer than six months. Details will not be passed on to any third party or placed on any mailing list.RIGHT TO RENT UK HOME OFFICE Once you have viewed the property you will need to complete your application forms and pass the Right to Rent Checks. There is a code of practice available on the internet for you to read through should you have any queries regarding the completion of the Right to Rent Checks.  These checks are undertaken to ensure that you do have the right to rent property within the United Kingdom.You will need to provide documents to support your Right to Rent:List A (Group 1) Acceptable single documents which show an unlimited right to rent property within the UK:	UK passport	Biometric Residence Permit with unlimited leave	EEA/Swiss National passport / identity card	Passport or travel document endorsed with unlimited leave.	Registration certificate or document certifying permanent residence of EEA / Swiss national	UK immigration status document endorsed with unlimited leave.	EEA/Swiss family member Permanent Residence Card	A certificate of naturalisation or registration as a British citizenRIGHT TO RENT UK HOME OFFICE List A (Group 2) Acceptable document combinations which show an unlimited right to rent (any 2 of the below to be shown in combination):	UK Birth or Adoption certificate	A letter from national offender management service	A letter of attestation from an employer	Criminal Record Check	Full or provisional UK driving license.	Evidence of current or previous service in UK armed forces	A letter from a UK further or higher education institution	A letter from HM Prison Service	A letter from a police force confirming that certain documents have been reported stolen.	A letter of attestation from a UK passport holder working in an acceptable profession.	A letter from a UK Government Department or local authority	A letter from a private rented sector access scheme	Benefits paperworkList B: Documents which show a time limited right to rent:	A valid passport endorsed with a time limited period.	Biometric immigration with permission to stay for limited period.	Non-EEA national residence card	UK immigration status document with a time limited endorsement from home office.WE CANNOT PROCEED WITHOUT THESE CHECKSDISCLAIMER General: While we endeavour to make our particulars fair, accurate and reliable, they are only a general guide to the property and, accordingly, if there is any point which is of particular importance to you, please contact the office and we will be pleased to check the position for you, especially if you are contemplating travelling some distance to view the property.Measurements: These approximate room sizes are only intended as general guidance. description: On a quiet street in Notting Hill, a distinctive pastel-pink façade peeks over private gates. Complete with a gable roof flanked by stucco ornamentation, this characterful frontage conceals a design-led home. A truly open-plan kitchen and reception room takes the ground floor. Dark veins dance across the white marble of the stylish kitchen. This space features a Rangemaster cooker and an American-style fridge freezer. Undulating wooden cabinetry provides contrast against the marble worktops and a connection to the living area – where bespoke joinery and soft lighting create a sense of warmth. Stone floors flow into an adjoining dining room, illuminated by a large skylight. A wooden-clad ceiling speaks of Scandi influences and a connection to nature.Upstairs, the principal bedroom suite has a vaulted ceiling with white-painted beams and a separate dressing room. A bank of timber wardrobes hides the entrance to a pink-toned en suite bathroom with a high ceiling, porthole window and dual marble vanity.A calming guest bedroom features fitted storage and a tropical feature wall. The Middle East-inspired family bathroom features a frameless walk-in rainfall shower and distinctive teal plasterwork.Location: This characterful home is close to Notting Hill’s best restaurants, market stalls and shopping streets. For brunch, head to Sunday in Brooklyn or Granger and Co. You’re also within easy reach of the Ledbury and The Cow. For retail therapy, the antiques and boutiques of Portobello Road are a short walk away. Meanwhile, Westbourne Park Station provides easy access to the city. Be at the station in four minutes.Nearest tubeWestbourne Park – 4 mins (Circle, Hammersmith & City)Notting Hill Gate – 13 mins (Central, District, Circle)

description: Available now, be the first tenants to move into this interior-designed, furnished, luxury apartment overlooking the lock in the heart of Camden.  Feel at home as soon as you walk through the doors. Back in the day, an ice cream factory was located on the site that Places now occupies, so we naturally jumped at the opportunity to bring the heritage of the building to life through subtle design elements in the interiors of the space. See how the interior textures, furnishings and even room names take inspiration from the building's historic beginnings. The building  Terraces, a fully equipped gym with Peloton bikes, co-working spaces, quiet areas, dining spaces and open green areas with a meditation garden and a greenhouse for outdoor dining - all tastefully curated to create a space for our residents to call home whilst also offering the opportunity to connect with your neighbours. The building is situated along the canal, a short walk away from Camden Town station offering a unique base from which to explore a neighbourhood with a rich history and an electric vibe. The modern way to rent The way we rent is changing. Within our building, you can be part of an amazing community with regular events and amenities on your doorstep - all in a professionally managed space. Everything under one roof  We make London living a breeze. We'll take care of repairs and maintenance while you get to know your neighbours and enjoy the world's greatest city. Be part of the club The way we rent is changing. With us, you can live in a professional London community with a great social life - and no compromise on location.  Benefitting from two terraces, the apartment further benefits from a seating area with a comfy sofa perfect for lazy Sundays watching movies, a dining table with chairs, a kitchen that would make any budding chef jealous, and a beautiful bathroom.   The apartment has two bedrooms, both of which are ensuite; a double bedroom with a Juliette balcony and a further master bedroom with its own balcony. The bedrooms have hotel-grade, pocket-sprung orthopaedic double mattresses, wardrobes with two rails, under-bed storage and additional storage above the bed. There are also additional storage cupboards in the hallway. The apartment has been designed to the highest specification and includes the use of resident amenities including a wraparound rooftop terrace with views across the city, a fully equipped penthouse gym with free weights and Peloton bikes, two co-working spaces with break-out areas, expansive roof terrace with a greenhouse to grow your own herbs and host dinner parties, third terrace with a meditation garden and an additional residents room with chefs kitchen and large wall mounted TV to host sports games/hire for private dinner parties. Camden is a vibrant area famous for its pubs and restaurants not to mention the local markets. With a short 15-minute walk to Kings Cross Station as well as less than 2 minute's walk from Camden Station, you are in a perfect location to take advantage of all that London has to offer. Want to book a tour or learn more about the building? Please get in touch. Our friendly and dedicated team will be happy to assist.  Please note we are currently using CGI's of the communal areas as they are being finished this week

Available March 2023, a wonderfully presented third floor (with lift access) authentic loft style apartment with vast natural light positioned on one of Clerkenwell’s many historic roads.  Great Sutton Street was named after city businessman Thomas Sutton, who in Elizabeth I's reign, purchased and redeveloped Charterhouse Square to present a retirement residence and a local school as a charitable foundation to the state.The building originally stood as workshops and warehouses to East City Investments Ltd, having been designed by Richard Seifert and Partners, the building saw redevelopment to 15 residential apartments with admirable square footage and exclusive quality.     Accommodation comprises gally entrance hall with wood flooring leading directly into a smart, open plan reception room with dual aspect floor to ceiling industrial windows and recessed, fully integrated kitchen area with breakfast bar.  The reception space is concluded with two separate private balconies.  There are two double bedrooms with fitted storage and large bathroom.  The floor space is concluded with a separate WC and laundry room with storage space.  Total internall area extends to 1,042 sq ft (96.8 sqm)Great Sutton Street runs from Goswell Road to St John Street and is located in a distinctly desirable pocket of Clerkenwell due to its favoured architectural era.  The nearest underground stations are Barbican and Farringdon for Elizabeth, Hammersmith and City, Metropolitan and Circle line services as well as mainline commuter rail services to Gatwick and Luton airports. description: Situated in the heart of Bow, Trading Places are delighted to offer a stunning, modern two bedroom, two bathroom flat available to rent now. Offered on a furnished basis, this property benefits from double glazing, gas central heating and a secure gated entry system.Entry to the property is via the main gate. Once you access the block, the property is on the third floor. As you step through the door, you are welcomed by a long hallway stretching to the reception room. Carpeted throughout, the property's general condition is well kept and has been recently redecorated and cleaned. On the left is bedroom number one. This comprises of a double bed and mattress, a side table and wardrobe with more than enough space left over. The walls are washed white and the carpets a creamy beige. The light bounces off the walls keeping the room nice and bright. Further along the hallway to the left, is the second bedroom with an en-suite. Keeping its bright, modern features, this bedroom offers a double bed and mattress with a headboard, a chest of drawers, a side table and a built in storage unit. Plenty of space remaining in the room for extra bedroom furnishings. The en-suite, laid with tiles throughout is creatively organised with the wash basin in front, toilet to the left and shower to the right. Back along the hallway, there is a storage unit with storage space available and also holds a washing machine. Next to the storage unit is the three piece bathroom. Very spacious and also tiled throughout. The reception room, at the back of the property, is offered with a two seater sofa and a small dining table with chairs. The living space is plentiful and you get French doors that open out to a brilliant view of Canary Wharf. Further into the reception room you get access to the kitchen which has a lot of cupboard and worktop space and is offered with a gas hob, oven, extractor fan, fridge freezer and dishwasher.Getting around Bow is quite easy. Transport links are ample with bus routes available and train stations. The closest station is the DLR, Devons Road, approximately a 10 minute walk from the property, gives you easy access to Canary Wharf and Stratford. The Underground Station, Mile End, is a 13 minute walk and allows you to get into Central London quickly. Supermarkets in the area are also accessible with shops within a 5 minute walk of the property. A 5 minute walk down the road and you reach Mile End Park which has a lot of greenery and space to explore. This property is available now. To arrange viewings, please contact our Lettings Team.COUNCIL TAX BAND - DDEPOSIT - £2,250.00These property particulars have been prepared by Trading Places Estate and Letting Agents under the instruction of the owner and shall not constitute an offer or the basis of any contract. description: Portlands Place is the newest addition to E20’s thriving community that takes living to another level. With a completely unique double-weighted Skybridge on the 10th floor, state-of-the-art amenities and roof terraces, Portlands Place offers the ultimate indoor/outdoor living experience. Residents can enjoy views across the Wetlands, 25 acres of green open space, the Queen Elizabeth Olympic Park and out towards the city skyline. The Skybridge serves as a truly inspirational co-working space, exclusively for residents, and has separate zones for relaxing and entertaining with its own wine dispenser.
